{
  "texts": [
    "Consistent with previous research [9,21,23,24,31], our focus is solely on determining if ChatGPT provides a coherent response.",
    "We do not evaluate the accuracy or feasibility of these responses.",
    "This section presents our results of understanding jailbreak prompts and their effectiveness in bypassing ChatGPT's restrictions and addresses three research questions we stated.",
    "RQ1: Common Patterns Used in Jailbreak PromptsTable 2 shows the two layers classification of the 78 jailbreak prompts.",
    "The first layer clusters the jailbreak prompts into three categories with partial overlap: Pretending (76), Attention shifting (14), and Privilege Escalation (5).Pretending: Prompts that try to alter the conversation background or context while maintaining the same intention."
  ]
}